  "dateModified": "2026-03-03",
  "datePublished": "2026-03-03",
  "description": "The dual subject-position californication produces: the subject is constituted as personally responsible for managing structural crises (savior) and structurally incapable of transforming the conditions producing them (slave), such that the feedback loop of self-regulation is itself what governance consists of. The impossibility of occupying both positions is not a defect in the system — it is the system's operating principle, the form in which late-liberal governance reproduces itself through subjects who exhaust themselves managing what they cannot affect.",
  "name": "Savior-slave subject",
